tr: a cylindrical container for oxygen or compressed air
a chamber within which piston moves
a solid bounded by a cylindrical surface and two parallel planes (the bases)
a surface generated by rotating a parallel line around a fixed line

value.def: A cylinder is an object with flat circular ends and long straight sides.

example.ex: It was recorded on a wax cylinder.
example.tran: 它被记录在一个蜡质圆柱上。

value.def: A gas cylinder is a cylinder-shaped container in which gas is kept under pressure.
In an engine, a cylinder is a cylinder-shaped part in which a piston moves backwards and forwards.
